      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:4:3:163:6",
      "text": [
        " حَدُّ عَرَفَاتٍ مِنَ الْمَأْزِمَيْنِ إِلَى أَقْصَى الْمَوْقِفِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Muhammad Bin Ismail, from Ali Bin Al Numan, from Ibn Muskan, from Abu Baseer, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘A boundary of Arafaat is from Al-Mazameen up to the end of the Pausing Station’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "6. A number of our people have narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from Muhammad ibn ‘Isma‘il from Ali ibn al-Nu’man from ibn Muskan from abu Basir who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘The boundary of ‘Arafat is from al-Mazemin to the end of the station.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
